## The Bezel Alternative

For buyers with active lifestyles, the bezel setting completely eliminates the corner chip risk. A square bezel encircles all four sides of the princess diamond with a metal rim, providing 360-degree structural protection.

**[Bezel Solitaire in Platinum — $1,550](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/bezel-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-296647?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
Complete corner protection in platinum. The most structurally secure option for a princess cut.

**[Bezel Solitaire in 14K White Gold — $1,310](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/bezel-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-296642?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
More affordable bezel option.

**Trade-off:** Bezel settings cover the four corners entirely. The sharp-cornered look that makes princess cut distinctive from above is partially obscured. If you want the visible corners, use V-prong solitaire with all four corners confirmed. If you want maximum protection, use bezel.

