## The Corner Fracture Rule at Larger Sizes

The corner chip risk scales with stone size. Larger face-up area = larger corners = more surface exposed to impact.

| Carat Size | Corner Length (approx) | Eye-Clean VS Risk | V-prong Priority |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0.5ct | 2.7mm | Low | Medium |
| 1ct | 3.0mm | Medium | High |
| 1.5ct | 3.5mm | Medium-High | High |
| 2ct | 3.7mm | High | Critical |
| 3ct | 4.3mm | Very High | Critical — V-prong + VS1 mandatory |

For 3ct analysis: see [3 Carat Princess Cut Diamond Price](https://diamondcritics.com/3-carat-princess-cut-diamond-price/) — the Corner Fracture Rule section.

